<br>
I am sad to say it, but I generally see at least 1 piece of Iksar armor rot on most Hate raids due to there being no Iskar on the raid itself.  I'm sorry to say, but as a CoG raid commander there is not much I can do to alleviate this situation and prevent it from happening except to say if you are an Iksar warrior, come on down.  I wish I could organize and find a warrior or two to take up before hand, but if none show up, thats how it is.  I do not think it would be fair for me to keep a small list of people to call on if no one from that class shows up.  At best that would be favoritism.  So all I can suggest is to show on up and hope something for your class drops.  As a side note, in general there is always the possibility for something for every class to drop in either plane even if your armor doesnt generally drop from there.  The chests in Hate and Cubes in Fear drop armor from the other plane.  Also in Hate there is the second floor and just the chance for other weird weapon and shield drops.  I would encourage everyone to go to both planes.  Not just for the loot as well, but to help out the other classes.  It's not really fair for everyone to help out the clerics and enchanters in Hate only to not have any of them go to Fear.  Also, it'd kinda suck for the clerics to keep dying because they have no backup healers in their groups because the druids see no point in going to Hate.  But, this being a purely voluntary group, there's no way to do anything other than ask.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
